      "content": "The argument that a loss of a traditional majority weakens cultural identity is a common trope among traditionalist thinkers, but it often ignores the resilience of democratic institutions to adapt to new realities. Historically, Western democracies have successfully integrated diverse populations by evolving their social norms and legal frameworks to accommodate new values, rather than collapsing under demographic pressure. The stability of a democracy depends more on the quality of its institutions and the commitment of its citizens to shared civic principles than on maintaining a specific ethnic or cultural majority.",
