      "role": "user",
      "content": "I hear you, but isn't \"civic principles\" itself a concept rooted in specific Western traditions? To be real, many people feel that when you have a mass shift in the population, the core values that built the system get diluted or replaced by totally different social priorities. If the cultural groundwork that makes a democracy work starts to erode because the majority of people no longer share the same historical heritage, isn't it a legitimate concern that the institutions themselves might become unstable or effectively change into something else entirely? Like, can a system survive if the foundation of its identity is fundamentally altered?",
